caption.text:
⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀𝐄𝐗𝐏𝐄𝐂𝐓𝐀𝐓𝐈𝐎𝐍𝐒⠀࿓࿔
⠀
⠀
⠀
⠀
001. | ⠀⠀Literacy
⠀
English isn't my first language, so i might make mistakes myself.
A few typos and grammar mistakes are fine, as we make those sometimes. It's not nice to see them pop up everywhere though!
⠀
I don't have an ideal length I'd like to receive, but please make sure to give me enough to work with. It's not that hard to find be detailed, is it?
Still, quality over quantity.
I won't accept one-liners though.
⠀
⠀
⠀
002. |⠀⠀ Powerplay
⠀
Sometimes you might find yourself wanting to force your actions on my character. Aside for the progress of a starter, i will not tolerate that kinda behavior.
We got our own characters to control after all.
⠀
⠀
⠀
⠀
003. | ⠀⠀Themes
⠀
I have no triggers that I'm aware of, but if you have any, please inform me as we plot!
⠀
There are certain areas I'm not that experienced, but I'm more than willing to explore new themes.
This account will most likely deal with mature themes, so if you can't handle even the basic things like aggression, foul language (...etc), then this might not be the account for you.
⠀
Overly romantic or sexual themes will be reserved my my character's love interest only.
Please don't try to force a ship on me.
⠀
⠀
⠀
⠀
004. | ⠀⠀ Plotting
⠀
Once we have the main themes sorted out, i expect us to devise a plot.
But don't be afraid to add plot twists, these are so thrilling aha! And they get the rp going too.
⠀
Our plot doesn't always have to be that detailed, or else it will be so predictable.
Also, if you are unhappy with the plot then please let me know!
We want an rp that is enjoyable for us both.
⠀
⠀
⠀
⠀
005. | ⠀⠀Timing
⠀
Don't spam me for a reply.
I can, and most likely will ignore your pleas for a response.
I have a life out of here, and my muse to write changes throughout the day, but I'm always trying my best to give you a proper response.
That might take time so please, respect my timing.
⠀
If i haven't replied within four days then feel free to reach out for me.
If I'll take a while to reply then I'll let you know.
⠀
⠀
That's all. Thanks for taking the time to read this.

caption.text:
The first look of Call of Duty Mobile post the official launch in India.

The game seems to be working on multiple levels drawing inspiration from multiple titles and giving the best of both worlds.

The autos hooting feature makes it ridiculously easy to shoot but the range at which it gets activated is a key quotient. May be sticking to the manual controls would be a far better option as the game unfolds for the future stages.

Graphic quality is subliminal as most of us who have played the PC  versions of COD would expect, and the physical realism is well though for.

Overall the game seems great fun and the 5v5 layout does remind you of the Rainbow Six times but as compared to the Warehouse of PUBG Mobile, personally, I find the COD maps to be more detailed with multiple points for both assault based players as well as camp snipers.

Looking forward to taking my squad into the COD universe.

@callofdutymobile for such an exciting alternative to the usually boring world of mobile gaming.

A big shoutout to @esportsfedindia for making this video possible at this hour. The training and streaming centre is well equipped for gamers to review games as well as practicing with the squad.

Mickey and Minnie set off on an adventure in search of a missing friend. On their journey they travel across many locations. Various stage themes consists of Pirates, Castles, and even a fun house. At the end of each act or location the duo encounters a Disney villain each from various franchises. When the duo finally finds there lost friend it is revealed to be Alice form Alice in Wonderland!

Very interesting note here is that the game was originally developed in japan on the famicom by HudsonSoft! When localized here in  the US many regional differences (assumably due to being published state side by capcom) in characters were either omitted or changed completely in the final cut. An Example of this is on the famicom the final boss you encounter is Cheshire Cat from Alice in wonderland and the US localization replaces the villain with Witch Hazel. Another instance is on Hooks ship on famicom you fight Captain Hook and on the IS version you fight peg Leg Pete. There are also rumors of a Hidden Mickey located somewhere on the rom board of the cartridge !

RU: Два года Cuphead и 5 миллионов проданных копий

Разработчики из Studio MDHR в честь двухлетия игры Cuphead похвастались успехами своего проекта – игра уже успела продаться тиражом в 5 миллионов копий! Это суммарные продажи с трёх доступных платформ: PC, Xbox One и Switch. Весьма неплохо, особенно с учётом того, что во время разработки некоторым членам команды пришлось заложить свои дома, чтобы завершить работу над проектом. Прямо сейчас команда работает над дополнением «The Delicious Last Course», которое добавит нового играбельного персонажа, уровни и боссов. Оно выйдет в 2020 году.
----------
EU: Two years of Cuphead and 5 million copies sold

Developers from Studio MDHR in honor of the biennium of the Cuphead game boasted the success of their project - the game has already sold out in a circulation of 5 million copies! These are total sales from the three available platforms: PC, Xbox One and Switch. Very good, especially considering that during the development some team members had to lay down their homes in order to complete work on the project. Right now, the team is working on the “The Delicious Last Course” add-on, which will add a new playable character, levels and bosses. It will be released in 2020.

The game seems to be working on multiple levels drawing inspiration from multiple titles and giving the best of both worlds.

The autos hooting feature makes it ridiculously easy to shoot but the range at which it gets activated is a key quotient. May be sticking to the manual controls would be a far better option as the game unfolds for the future stages.

Graphic quality is subliminal as most of us who have played the PC  versions of COD would expect, and the physical realism is well though for.

Overall the game seems great fun and the 5v5 layout does remind you of the Rainbow Six times but as compared to the Warehouse of PUBG Mobile, personally, I find the COD maps to be more detailed with multiple points for both assault based players as well as camp snipers.

Looking forward to taking my squad into the COD universe.

@callofdutymobile for such an exciting alternative to the usually boring world of mobile gaming.

**Early Patch Notes** -
Content creators had the opportunity to play Apex Legends Season 3 early and this is a combination of observations and patch notes created by them. -
May be slightly different upon launch -
———Charge Rifle——— •Energy sniper, takes Extended Energy Mag, Scope and Sniper Stock as attachments •Works similarly to alt-fire Havoc, except consumes 1 ammo per shot, deals much more damage, and... •The initial targeting laser deals small damage before the powerful hit. Up to 75 damage per shot (body) -
———Hop-ups———
-
•Disruptor Rounds removed •Skullpiercer Rifling removed •Double Tap: Fires 2 shots in rapid succession with every trigger pull. For the G7 Scout and the Eva-8 Shotgun. (Purple) •Anvil Reciever: Makes semi auto shots do more damage, with a slower rate of fire and uses two ammo. For the R-301 and VK47-Flatline. (Gold) -
——Legend Changes (not confirmed)—— -
•Pathfinder's grapple has been altered. The grapple itself moves slower and the delay before Pathfinder moves toward it is longer. (it's only very slight, but will require relearning of timing) •Characters inside Gibraltar's Dome Shield have reduced ability cooldown time. •Gibraltar and Bangalore's Ultimate damage increased •Wraith in phase/portal now takes Ring damage •Bloodhound's Ultimate duration increased -
———Item Changes——— -
•Golden Backpack perk changed to Guardian Angel: Revived allies have increased shields and health when you revive them (50 shields and 70 health on revive) •Golden Body Shield takes the old Fast Use perk from the backpack
-
———Gun Changes———
- •Longbow fire rate reverted to pre-S2 buff •Longbow and Wingman base headshot damage adjusted to around Skullpiercer level •R99 Level 3 magazine sized reduced from 30 to 27 •L-Star has a new optic for clearer aiming, as well as increased projectile size •All-around shotgun buff, projectile size is larger
.

Did you know that they made a four player adapter for the NES? They actually made two! This is one of them - the NES Satellite. You just plug the little piece into the controller ports on the NES, plug four controllers into the big part, make sure you have six C batteries powering it, be playing one of the like five compatible games, and then you'll be rocking out four player style with hi-tech infrared technology!

There are only a handful of games that actually go with it. I think the only one I own that supports more than two players is MONOPOLY. Alternatively you can just use it as a wireless controller extension which was actually pretty cool in the late 80's when it came out.

This actually belongs to my good friend Mike, but I've been holding onto it indefinitely for him. He's always wanted to use it to play A Nightmare On Elm Street. One day that dream may still may become reality.

We're live with #overwatch and #deadbydaylight  leggoo!
